Package me.labconnect.webapp.models.testing

Class UnitTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.labconnect.webapp.models.testing.UnitTest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Tester
    public class UnitTest
extends java.lang.Object
implements Tester
    A model of a single unit test, with one tester class and a correct output.

    The test is done by comparing the output of the tester with the output generated by the example implementation

    Version:
    01.05.2021
    Author:
    Berkan Åžahin

      • UnitTest

        public UnitTest​(java.lang.String name,
                java.nio.file.Path testerClass,
                java.nio.file.Path exampleImpl,
                long timeLimitMilliseconds)
         throws java.io.IOException,
                BadExampleException
        Creates a new unit test from the given tester and generates the correct output from the example implementation
        Parameters:
        name - The name of this test
        testerClass - The tester class, which is a singular java file with a main method
        exampleImpl - The example implementation supplied by the instructor
        timeLimitMilliseconds - The maximum time for the unit test in milliseconds. A value of 0 denotes no time limit
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If an I/O problem is encountered while processing the implementation or tester files
        BadExampleException - If the example implementation fails the unit test
        Implementation Note:
        the tester class is copied to the assignment directory, therefore it is safe to delete it afterwards
